pt:Chunk_101_15 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_5 ;
    ns1:text """Background

This Policy sets out the principles that guide the University in managing research data and demonstrating its continued commitment to excellence and integrity in research.

Research Data Management affects everyone at UEA who is engaged in research, at whatever level and whatever their discipline.  ‚ÄòData‚Äô exist in a wide variety of forms across all UEA research fields and the principles laid out here are equally relevant to images of artefacts in art history, as computer models in game theory, as sequences in genetics and as spectra in structure characterisation.  From new students to experienced researchers, ensuring that research materials are well managed throughout the research project, and beyond, enables UEA‚Äôs research to have the greatest possible reach and benefit to the academic community and the wider public."""^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_101_16 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_-1 ;
    ns1:text """Review

This Research Data Management Policy sets out the University‚Äôs position on the management of Research Data.  This is a rapidly-evolving area and the supporting document on Research Data

Management Procedures and Guidance will be updated as the resources and infrastructure to support Research Data management are developed throughout the University.

This Policy will be reviewed and updated by the University Research Ethics Committee (UREC) and recommendations will be made to the University Research Executive, and thereafter to Senate before 31 December 2025."""^^xsd:string .

