pt:Chunk_126_10 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_-1 ;
    ns1:text "2.2 Any research activity where research data may be created or re-used should include at the outset a data management plan. These plans are to be updated and maintained during the life of the research project."^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_126_11 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_0 ;
    ns1:text "Researchers, in particular principal investigators, are responsible for creating and updating a research data management plan for research projects in accordance with funder and university expectations."^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_126_12 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_-1 ;
    ns1:text "2.3 For data underpinning published research findings, reasonable efforts should be made to make them available for access and re-use with as few restrictions as possible, where legally, ethically and commercially appropriate. This should be done in a timely manner, no later than 12 months after publication or as soon as required by publishers and funders."^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_126_13 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_-1 ;
    ns1:text "2.4 Where it can be made accessible, research data should be deposited in a data service, disciplinary data repository, or the University‚Äôs Open Access repository as appropriate."^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_126_14 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_-1 ;
    ns1:text "Researchers are responsible for identifying, preparing, and transferring data for sharing and/or preservation to appropriate repositories, including the University‚Äôs repository. In special cases, Library and IT Services may facilitate transfer and dissemination (e.g. very large datasets or sensitive data)."^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_126_15 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_-1 ;
    ns1:text "2.5 Unless explicitly stated in a collaborative contract where Intellectual Property Right (IPR) or data responsibility is retained by another institution, all research data must be registered with the University by creating a metadata record in the University‚Äôs repository, even if the data is hosted elsewhere (e.g., in a third-party repository)."^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_126_16 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_9 ;
    ns1:text "Researchers are responsible for registering their research data by creating a metadata record in the University‚Äôs repository or by sending a link to an existing repository record to the Library‚Äôs Open Research team. Metadata and data records created in the University repository are considered registered. The Library will be responsible for holding and making publicly available these metadata records."^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_126_17 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_6 ;
    ns1:text "2.6 Research data that substantiate research findings or is of long-term value should be preserved in an appropriate format with adequate documentation for verification and reuse for a minimum of 10 years from project end or as long as is mandated by funder, ethical, legal, or regulatory requirements."^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_126_18 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_22 ;
    ns1:text "2.7 A data access or availability statement should be included in published papers. It should describe where and on what terms supporting research data may be accessed."^^xsd:string .

