    ns1:text """Colofon  

From the TPM  Mission Statement:    

The Faculty of Technology, Policy and Management combines insights from the engineering sciences with insights from the humanities and the social sciences. The Faculty‚Äôs mission is to develop robust models and designs in order to solve the complex challenges of today‚Äôs networked, urbanized knowledge society.  

The Faculty is comprised of three closely collaborating departments, each with a different perspective on addressing these complex societal challenges: systems, governance and values. The smart combination of these three perspectives is at the core of Comprehensive Engineering, and is the main thrust of the Faculty. The main application domains of the Faculty, in which the majority of its research projects can be clustered, are: energy, climate, mobility, ICT, water, and cyber."""^^xsd:string .

