pt:Chunk_22_5 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_1 ;
    ns1:text """4 Handling Research Data  

Freie Universit√§t Berlin encourages researchers to structure and archive their research data and to make these accessible in accordance with the FAIR principles. These principles aim to make digital data more findable, accessible, interoperable, and reusable. Research data should be managed in a way that is compatible with the relevant subject-specific practices, with the principles of ethical research,‚Äâ13 and the guidelines and recommendations issued by professional associations in the relevant subject.14 Freie Universit√§t Berlin adheres to the principles of the ‚ÄúSorbonne Declaration on Research Data Rights,‚Äù‚Äâ15 and recommends that researchers work on the guiding principle of ‚Äúas open as possible, as closed as necessary.‚Äù"""^^xsd:string .

