pt:Chunk_31_2 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_-1 ;
    ns1:text """II.   Importance of Research Data Management  

RDM enables researchers to organize, store, access, reuse and build upon digital research data. RDM is essential to Canadian researchers‚Äô capacity to securely preserve and use their research data throughout their research projects, reuse their data over the course of their careers and, when appropriate, share their data. Furthermore, as an acknowledged component of research excellence, strong RDM practices support researchers in achieving scientific rigor and enable collaboration in their fields (Tri-Agency Research Data Management Policy - Frequently Asked Questions)."""^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_31_20 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_-1 ;
    ns1:text """2)   External Resources  

Digital Research Alliance of Canada, Research Data Management   
    
The First Nations Principles of OCAP¬Æ   
    
The CARE Principles for Indigenous Data Governance:   
    
Research Data Management Terminology:"""^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_31_21 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_21 ;
    ns1:text """3)   Internal Policies  

Academic Integrity in Research Policies and Procedures   
Information Technology Policy   
