# Research Data Guidelines  

## of Justus Liebig University Giessen  

On 29th October 2018 Justus Liebig University Giessen has given itself research data guidelines. These guidelines define the principles on which members of the university are to handle research data. Please note that only the German version of the regula∆üons is official and legally binding. The English version is for informa∆üve purposes only. The original document can be found here.  

Former versions:   


 Presidium Approval 
Guideline 12.12.2017 29.10.2018   

Research data are the founda∆üon and the result of scien∆üfic work. The responsible handling of research data ensures replicability, verifiability and reusability of research results and is thus a fundamental aspect of good scien∆üfic prac∆üce. Justus Liebig University acknowledges the importance of sustainable research data management and regulates the handling of research data for all members of the university in the following principles, irrespec∆üve of data protec∆üon requirements and the guidelines for ensuring good scien∆üfic prac∆üce.  """^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_36_1 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_4 ;
    ns1:text "Research data refers to all data that are gained in the process of doing research through observa∆üon, collec∆üon, measurement, experiment, simula∆üon and processing or that are the result thereof. This also includes the documenta∆üon and so≈åware necessary for the understanding of such data. Depending on scien∆üfic discipline and faculty culture, research data can exist in different types, aggrega∆üon levels and formats.   "^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_36_2 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_-1 ;
    ns1:text "Research data management includes all handling of research data, ranging from planning the data collec∆üon and storage to assuring data quality and processing data to making data available or publishing it. Research data management is oriented towards the current professional standards and takes discipline-specific requirements into account. Handling research data will be documented in a research data management plan at an early stage of a research project and, if necessary, is to be adjusted to the process of the respec∆üve project.   "^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_36_3 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_-1 ;
    ns1:text "According to research data management, researchers are required to secure research data safely, appropriately process and document research data, and store research data in the long-term (at least for 10 years). The protec∆üon of personal data as well as compliance to copyright and legi∆ümate interest of third par∆ües must be ensured. The principal inves∆ügators of research projects are responsible for guaranteeing these processes.   "^^xsd:string .

