pt:Chunk_92_19 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_-1 ;
    ns1:text "Plans should explicitly cover: ownership; standards/methodologies for data collection and management; ethical and privacy issues (including GDPR considerations if any personal data is involved); short-term storage and long-term preservation and/or deletion; data sharing and access/ temporary or long-term restrictions."^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_92_2 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_2 ;
    ns1:text "Before a project begins, a research Data Management Plan (DMP) must be completed."^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_92_20 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_-1 ;
    ns1:text """Where research is undertaken in partnership or under contract with a third party, a collaboration agreement must be signed before the start of the research that clearly addresses data ownership and partner responsibility for data storage.

Data collected during a project where the University is responsible for data storage must be stored on the University network, to ensure that it is suitably protected against accidental loss or damage and against unauthorised access"""^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_92_21 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_7 ;
    ns1:text "The University provides a secure Research Data Storage Service (RDSS) for this purpose, which ensures that only authorised staff can access project data, and that data can be restored in the event of accidental loss or damage."^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_92_22 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_7 ;
    ns1:text "Temporary use of portable devices and storage and/or the University‚Äôs approved cloud service during, for example, field research, processing or collaboration must comply with the University‚Äôs Data Storage Policy."^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_92_23 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_-1 ;
    ns1:text "Data placed on temporary storage must be transferred back onto the RDSS as soon as the requirement for temporary storage has ended, to minimise the risk of reputational damage and/or litigation caused from lost, stolen or intercepted data."^^xsd:string .

pt:Chunk_92_24 a ns1:chunk ;
    pt:describes pt:Topic_7 ;
    ns1:text """Research proposals should consider whether storage requirements may exceed those currently offered by the University. Any such potential requirement should be discussed in advance of the application with both Information Services (infrastructure) and REIS (funding).

